        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:57PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Harris Ferry, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harris Ferry, Rightangle, Vianna, Redhouse, Jackson Ferry, Olivers,
Mina, Union City, Bybee, and Hunt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
